# intuition
Matrices were first used to simplify solving systems of linear equations, and get all their natural properties from that.

- $A^{\dagger} = (A^{*})^{T} = (A^{t})^{*}$
- $A^{*}$ - is every element conjugated, see [[complex_number]]
- $A^{T}$ transposing, that is making the x-axis the y-axis.

# rigour
- [[trace]] := the sum of the main diagonal
- Discriminant := $t^2 - 4\det$
- semi := non-negative eigenvalues
- definite := real eigenvalues
